  "prompt": "Create a modular system flow diagram illustrating the interaction between core elements of HelenKella's neurodivergence-driven innovation platform. Include the following components: 1. Neurodivergence as a Scalability Engine - ADHD as foresight (anticipating problems before they arise), Trauma literacy (designing systems that withstand disruption), OCD-like systemization (looping and refining for airtight execution). 2. Authenticity-First Branding - Building authentic connections with neurodivergent and trauma-aware audiences, Creating a safe, unapologetic space for individuals who do not fit into sanitized ecosystems. 3. Chaos-to-Order Execution - Transforming chaotic ideas into scalable, high-functioning systems, Rapid adaptability and evolution through strategic breakdown and rebuilding cycles. 4. Humor-Based Engagement - Using dark humor and satire to build community resonance and engagement. 5. Platform & Ecosystem Design - A self-sustaining ecosystem fueled by neurodivergent insights, Ethical monetization models, and community-based growth, Survivability and scalability through continuous optimization loops. The diagram should visually represent the interconnections between these components, with an emphasis on dynamic loops, rapid feedback cycles, and emergent system growth. Use color and shape coding to distinguish between foundational, strategic, and operational components. Focus on illustrating the seamless flow between chaos, structure, and adaptability.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

